\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {3}{\ignorespaces c2c design-iteration disentangling. Five bars: v1/v2 baseline, v3 LoRA alone, ABL\_A (block coverage with v2 answer-span supervision), ABL\_B (full-response loss with last-block-only commit), v3 full. The pre-registered $80\%$ target and base test \texttt  {cmaj}{} of $79\%$ lines are visible. The $+0.0$ result for ABL\_B (full-response loss with $n_\text  {blocks}{=}1$) makes the ``block coverage is dominant'' story visually unambiguous. Generated by \texttt  {scripts/make\_paper\_figures.py}.}}{14}{figure.3}\protected@file@percent }
